West 58th Street South Side and looking East from 2214,a point midway between Broadway and Seventh Avenue and across the latter. The 58th Street Theatre as shown,occupies the site of a former 3 story stable and bears the numbers 206-202. The windowless structure appearing on the right occupies Numbers 214-208 and is in the rear of the American Fine Arts Building,#2I5 West 57th Street. (This set consists of a negative
and a positive.)
September I935

View in the same direction,showing the North Side of the Street and showing the 'Hotel Barbizon Plaza in the back-ground at 6th Avenue.

Broadway, east side, north from W. 58th to 59th Street, showing a two-story taxpayer that is to be demolished. This site, an Ehret property is to be improved with two distinctive apartment houses. A full account is to be found in the Herald Tribune of January 21, 1940. View 2 is limited to this block front. Central Park West is at the left of the extensive preceding view. There upon appears the Mayflower (61st to 62nd Streets) and the twin-towered Century Apartments(68nd to
63rd Streets).
May 21, 1939
Views 1,2
P. L. Sperr
